---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Soundvibes | Offline Voice-to-Text">
  <section class="mx-auto grid w-full max-w-6xl gap-12 px-6 pb-16 pt-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] lg:items-center">
    <div class="space-y-8" data-smoke="hero">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-white/80 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/70">
        Offline Speech-to-Text for Linux
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink sm:text-5xl">
        Capture voice notes without cloud latency, scripts, or surprises.
      </h1>
      <p class="max-w-xl text-lg text-ink/70">
        Soundvibes keeps your workflow local. Vulkan-only system dependencies, automatic model downloads,
        and a hotkey toggle flow that keeps capture under your control.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a
          class="rounded-full bg-ink px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-glow transition hover:-translate-y-0.5"
          href="#install"
        >
          Install with One Command
        </a>
        <a
          class="rounded-full border border-ink/20 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-ink transition hover:border-ink"
          href="docs"
        >
          Documentation
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-3 text-sm text-ink/70 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-mint"></span>
          Works fully offline
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-citrus"></span>
          Auto model download
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-coral"></span>
          No daemon babysitting
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-ink"></span>
          GitHub Releases only
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="glass-card rounded-3xl p-6">
      <div class="rounded-2xl bg-ink px-5 py-6 text-white" data-smoke="quickstart">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/60">Quickstart</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-2xl font-semibold">Two commands, done.</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-sm">
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/10 px-4 py-3">
            <p class="text-white/60">Start the daemon once</p>
            <code class="mt-2 block text-sm font-semibold text-white">sv daemon start</code>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/10 px-4 py-3">
            <p class="text-white/60">Hotkey your toggle</p>
            <code class="mt-2 block text-sm font-semibold text-white">sv</code>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-white/70">
          Models download automatically on first run. Bind the toggle to any hotkey in your environment.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 text-sm text-ink/70">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink/10 bg-white px-4 py-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-ink">Vulkan-only dependencies</p>
          <p>Keep setup lean with just Vulkan libraries on Linux.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink/10 bg-white px-4 py-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-ink">Auto model download</p>
          <p>Pick your language, let Soundvibes pull the model once.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink/10 bg-white px-4 py-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-ink">Fast toggling</p>
          <p>Toggle capture while you talk, transcripts land when you stop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink/10 bg-white px-4 py-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-ink">X11 & Wayland</p>
          <p>Works seamlessly on both, text appears right where your cursor is.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="workflow" class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50">Workflow</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-ink">A calm toggle rhythm.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-ink/70">
          Start the daemon once, then hotkey the toggle wherever you work. Soundvibes listens locally,
          trims silence, and prints the transcript when you toggle off.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink/70">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-mint text-ink">1</span>
            Launch the daemon with <span class="font-semibold text-ink">sv daemon start</span>.
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-citrus text-ink">2</span>
            Bind <span class="font-semibold text-ink">sv</span> to a hotkey and toggle capture.
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-coral text-ink">3</span>
            Transcript appears at cursor after you toggle off.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-card rounded-3xl p-6">
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-cloud px-6 py-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Everything offline.</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/70">
            No network calls. No cloud queue. Soundvibes stays on your device, using local models
            and a reliable on/off cadence that fits your daily flow.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink/10 bg-white px-4 py-4">
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50">Models</p>
              <p class="mt-2 font-semibold text-ink">Auto download on first run</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink/10 bg-white px-4 py-4">
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50">Audio</p>
              <p class="mt-2 font-semibold text-ink">Voice activity trimming built in</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="benefits" class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-6 md:flex-row md:items-end md:justify-between">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50">Why Soundvibes</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-ink">Focused tooling, fewer distractions.</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="max-w-lg text-lg text-ink/70">
        Soundvibes is designed for low-maintenance capture. Minimal dependencies keep the setup slim,
        while the model downloader handles the heavy lifting automatically.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="glass-card rounded-3xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-ink">Vulkan-only dependencies</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/70">
          Rely on Vulkan libraries and keep the rest of your system untouched.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-card rounded-3xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-ink">Automatic model download</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/70">
          Choose a size once, Soundvibes fetches the matching model the first time you run it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-card rounded-3xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-ink">GPU-accelerated speed</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/70">
          Uses your GPU for fast transcription without cloud latency.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50">Use cases</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-ink">Everyday voice capture, without friction.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-ink/70">
          Use Soundvibes for vibe coding, to drop short notes between meetings, or transcribe research
          thoughts. Everything stays local, so you can stay focused offline.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-3 text-sm text-ink/70">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-mint"></span>
            Daily voice notes and journaling
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-citrus"></span>
            Vibe coding narration and prompts
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-coral"></span>
            Research capture while offline
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-card rounded-3xl p-6">
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white px-5 py-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50">Session flow</p>
          <h3 class="mt-4 font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Stay in the zone.</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/70">
            Start the daemon once, then toggle capture whenever you want a short transcript. Minimal
            overhead, maximum focus.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-ink/10 px-3 py-1">Offline</span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-ink/10 px-3 py-1">Automatic models</span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-ink/10 px-3 py-1">Two commands</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-10 lg:flex-row lg:items-start lg:justify-between">
      <div class="max-w-xl">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50">FAQ</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-ink">Answers, without the noise.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-ink/70">
          Keep it simple. Soundvibes is built around the two commands you need, with models handled for you.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-4 lg:w-[55%]">
        <div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
          <p class="font-semibold text-ink">Does it run fully offline?</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/70">Yes. After the first model download, everything stays local.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
          <p class="font-semibold text-ink">How do I start and stop capture?</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/70">
            Start the daemon with <span class="font-semibold text-ink">sv daemon start</span>, then bind
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">sv</span> to a hotkey and toggle on/off.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
          <p class="font-semibold text-ink">How do I install it?</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/70">
            Run the install script: <code class="rounded bg-ink/10 px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kejne/soundvibes/main/install.sh | sh</code>. It handles everything automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="install" class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="rounded-3xl bg-ink px-8 py-12 text-white md:px-12">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/60">Installation</p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-semibold">One command to install.</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-sm text-white/70">
            The install script handles dependencies, downloads the binary, and sets up configuration automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <a
            class="rounded-full bg-white px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-ink transition hover:-translate-y-0.5"
            href="https://github.com/kejne/soundvibes/releases"
          >
            View GitHub Releases
          </a>
          <span class="text-xs text-white/60">Or use the install script below.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 rounded-2xl bg-white/10 p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/60">Quick Install</p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
          <code class="flex-1 rounded-xl bg-white/10 px-4 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-white">
            curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kejne/soundvibes/main/install.sh | sh
          </code>
          <button
            class="rounded-full bg-white/20 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:bg-white/30"
            onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText('curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kejne/soundvibes/main/install.sh | sh')"
          >
            Copy
          </button>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-white/70">
          The script auto-detects your distribution, installs dependencies, downloads the latest binary,
          and optionally sets up a systemd service. Supports Ubuntu, Debian, Arch, and Fedora.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-xs">
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 text-white/80">Auto-detects distro</span>
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 text-white/80">Installs dependencies</span>
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 text-white/80">Systemd service setup</span>
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 text-white/80">Wayland & X11 support</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white/5 p-5">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/60">Manual Download</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/70">
            Prefer to install manually? Download the binary directly from <a href="https://github.com/kejne/soundvibes/releases" class="text-white underline hover:text-white/80">GitHub Releases</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white/5 p-5">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/60">Non-Interactive</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/70">
            For automated setups, use <code class="rounded bg-white/10 px-1 py-0.5">--yes</code> flag:
            <code class="mt-1 block rounded bg-white/10 px-2 py-1 font-mono text-xs">./install.sh --yes</code>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
